    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.heading_13' => 'Error Handling Review Checklist (Pre-Release)',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.heading_14' => 'Team Standard (Strict) Error Handling',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.heading_15' => 'Operational Severity Matrix',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.heading_16' => 'Standard Postmortem Format (Template)',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.heading_2' => 'Current Fallbacks in the Project',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.heading_3' => 'Map Errors to Handle',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.heading_4' => 'Strategy Mapping Exception -> Response',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.heading_5' => 'Web Response Standards vs API',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.heading_6' => 'Example of an API Error Contract (Recommendation)',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.heading_7' => 'Minimum Logging & Context',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.heading_8' => 'Redaction of Messages to Users',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.heading_9' => 'Custom Error Page Templates',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_1' => 'Keep the application providing safe, clear and actionable responses.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_10' => '<code>user_id</code> (if any), tenant/account id (if multi-tenant).',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_11' => 'Log <code>request_id</code>, URL, HTTP method, and status code.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_12' => '<code>user_id</code> (if any), tenant/account id (if multi-tenant).',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_13' => 'Security guardrail checklist',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_14' => 'Masking sensitive data in the log (token, secret, password, card number).',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_15' => 'Make sure <code>APP_DEBUG=false</code> in production.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_16' => 'Masking sensitive data in the log (token, secret, password, card number).',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_17' => 'Retry and idempotency policy',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_18' => 'Critical operations (payments/orders) require idempotency keys to avoid duplication.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_19' => 'Non-critical operations can be directed to retry with backoff.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_2' => 'Separating known errors (expected) vs system errors (unexpected).',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_20' => 'Critical operations (payments/orders) require idempotency keys to avoid duplication.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_3' => 'Ensure the user experience remains good even if failure occurs.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_4' => 'Provides observability traces for fast investigation (log, context, request id).',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_5' => 'Web Response Standards vs API',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_6' => '<strong>API:</strong> return consistent structured JSON (<code>code</code>, <code>message</code>, <code>details</code>, <code>request_id</code>).',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_7' => '<strong>Web:</strong> display a custom error page (403/404/419/500) with a CTA back to the safe page.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_8' => '<strong>API:</strong> return consistent structured JSON (<code>code</code>, <code>message</code>, <code>details</code>, <code>request_id</code>).',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.item_9' => 'Minimum Logging & Context',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.lead' => 'Current 404 fallback, exception handling, and custom error pages.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.note_1' => 'Key principles: users get actionable messages, teams get enough technical logs for investigations.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.note_2' => 'Severity is determined by the business impact and extent of affected users, not just the type of exception.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_1' => 'The fallback is outside the auth middleware, so it can still appear for users who have not logged in.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_10' => '2. Triage: identify the most affected routes/services and business severity.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_11' => '3. Quick mitigation: rollback, feature flag off, or degrade mode.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_12' => '4. Permanent fix: root-cause fix + regression test.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_13' => '5. Postmortem: documentation of timeline, impact, action items, owner, and due date.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_14' => '2. The fallback route works and does not swallow application exceptions that need to be fixed.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_15' => '3. All API endpoints return a consistent JSON error format.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_16' => '4. The error log contains minimum context without leaking sensitive data.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_17' => '5. APP_DEBUG production is confirmed to be disabled.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_18' => '6. Timeout/dependency down scenarios are tested at least once before release.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_19' => '<strong>Rule mandatory:</strong> 5xx response to client must be generic; technical details only in internal logs.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_2' => 'All URLs that do not match route will fall into this fallback.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_20' => '<strong>Rule mandatory:</strong> each error log must have <code>request_id</code>, route, method, status code, and user context (if any).',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_21' => '<strong>Rule mandatory:</strong> there must be no sensitive data in the log (passwords, tokens, secrets, critical PII).',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_22' => '<strong>Rule mandatory:</strong> business exception mapping must be explicit (e.g. conflict -> 409, validation -> 422).',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_23' => '<strong>Required rule:</strong> fallback must not be used to cover bug 500.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_24' => '<strong>Mandatory rule:</strong> every Sev-1/Sev-2 incident must postmortem a maximum of 2x24 hours.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_25' => '<strong>Optional rule:</strong> critical endpoint adds idempotency key and scalable retry policy.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_26' => 'The fallback route leads to the page <code>pages.pages.authentication.general.error-404</code>.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_27' => 'Validation exception -> response 422 + field-level message.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_28' => 'Redaction of Messages to Users',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_29' => 'SOP Incident Error (Concise)',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_3' => 'Use fallback for route not found cases, not to hide application exceptions.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_30' => 'Error Handling Review Checklist (Pre-Release)',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_31' => 'Team Standard (Strict) Error Handling',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_4' => 'Exception authorization -> 403 with secure message (no sensitive details).',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_5' => 'Exception domain (eg insufficient stock) -> 409/422 according to context.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_6' => 'Unknown system exception -> 500 generic + complete log.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_7' => 'Provide further steps: retry, refresh, re-login, or contact support.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_8' => 'Use a consistent tone between error pages.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.step_9' => 'If necessary, display <code>request_id</code> so support can easily browse the logs.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.warn_1' => 'Avoid changing the error response format between endpoints randomly. Contract consistency is important for frontend/mobile clients.',
    'pages.skema.error-handling-dan-fallback.warn_2' => 'Postmortems focus on improving systems, not blaming individuals.',
