    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.item_1' => '<code>@@extends</code> for main layout inheritance.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.item_10' => 'If there is a translation, send the final text from the caller or send the key consistently.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.item_11' => 'Component â€œgod objectâ€ with too many optional props.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.item_12' => 'Partial that accesses query data directly.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.item_13' => 'Cross-page duplicate markup due to reluctant extraction.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.item_14' => 'Concern mixing: page specific styles/scripts are inserted into global partials.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.item_2' => '<code>@@include</code> for static/simple markup snippets.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.item_3' => '<code>@@component</code> for UI units that have slots/parameters.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.item_4' => '<code>&lt;x-...&gt;</code> for class-based/anonymous reusable components.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.item_5' => 'Suitable for repeating static blocks (toolbars, small breadcrumbs, hint text).',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.item_6' => 'Don\'t put heavy business logic on partials.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.item_7' => 'Partial: prefix underscore for internal-only, for example <code>_toolbar.blade.php</code>.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.item_8' => 'Component: domain name + function, for example <code>ui/info-card.blade.php</code>.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.item_9' => 'Props names use domain language (<code>title</code>, <code>badge</code>, <code>isActive</code>), avoid ambiguous generic names.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.lead' => 'Include/extend/component conventions, as well as guidance on when to use partial vs component.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.note_1' => 'Distinguish <code>layouts/partials</code> (global layout fragments) from <code>components</code> (API contracted reusable units/props).',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.note_2' => 'If your display needs are very different, create a new component variant. Avoid adding excessive props just to keep one component in use in all cases.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_1' => 'Use <code>component</code> if you need <code>props</code>, <code>slot</code>, input validation, and use across page domains.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_10' => '<strong>Required rule:</strong> partial must not query data or business logic.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_11' => '<strong>Optional rule:</strong> use class-based components if data normalization/formatting is needed before rendering.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_12' => '<strong>Optional rule:</strong> add a short docblock above the component to explain important props and usage examples.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_13' => 'Use <code>partial</code> if the display is simple, the context is already available from the parent, and there is no need for an API contract.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_14' => '1. Check first whether there is a similar partial/component that can be reused.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_15' => '<strong>Rule is mandatory:</strong> reusable components must have a clear <code>@@props</code> contract, safe default values, and domain-based prop names.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_2' => 'If you start to have a lot of optional parameters in partial, refactor it into a component.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_3' => 'If a component is only used once and without variations, consider downgrading it to partial.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_4' => '2. Determine the type: partial or component based on the decision matrix.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_5' => '3. Define input contracts clearly (props/slots/default values).',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_6' => '4. Make sure it is mobile compatible and meets the Metronic utility class.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_7' => '5. Review markup duplication and translation consistency before merge.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_8' => '<strong>Rule required:</strong> maximum <code>7 props</code> per component. If more, break it down into sub-components or use structured data objects.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.step_9' => '<strong>Rule required:</strong> maximum <code>2 named slots</code> + default slot. More than that usually indicates the component is too complex.',
    'pages.skema.komponen-blade-partial.warn_1' => 'If one partial is used in >3 locations with different variations, that is a strong signal for migration to components.',
